Hi Swati ,
       
    I understand your concern but its like junits are the work thats primarily done by a developer of a class I mean who understands its functionality . I am saying so because i think i had the same concept when i started with it but junit is a unit test a developer has to write for a class that he/she writes . So dont worry about it much and overall its more challenging than the real coding itself and will teach u a lot . For any books you can consult Junit recipies and get going ... All the best
